      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i keep getting a 500 error on the /api/v1/checkout endpoint whenever a user tries to apply a discount code. here is the relevant snippet from the logs:\n\n[2023-10-27 14:22:01] ERROR: Internal Server Error at /api/v1/checkout\n[2023-10-27 14:22:01] Traceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"/app/services/checkout_service.py\", line 142, in apply_discount\n    discount_val = discount_engine.calculate(cart_total, code)\n  File \"/app/services/discount_engine.py\", line 58, in calculate\n    return self._apply_seasonal_logic(base_price, code)\n  File \"/app/services/discount_engine.py\", line 89, in _apply_seasonal_logic\n    raise KeyError(f\"Invalid seasonal modifier for code: {code}\")\nKeyError: 'Invalid seasonal modifier for code: FALL20'\n\nseems like it's just failing on that specific code. any idea why it's hitting a KeyError there instead of just returning a validation error?",
